{"parentUuid":"f533531c-7e8c-42a0-aeee-c33b098c4f33","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed4149fd-c5a8-4db4-bdd2-38a556acc251","agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012BndCYW9vMsaCveqgWP5w2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Implementation progress — usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\n2\t\n3\t## Status: COMPLETE\n4\t\n5\tAll plan items built, all tests green, docs updated, self-check done,\n6\tsurface-delta.md written. Ready for the coordinator's final report / handoff\n7\tto testing.\n8\t\n9\t## DONE\n10\t\n11\tTest-first, unit-level red->green recorded per unit:\n12\t\n13\t- T1 CSV encoding facade: tests written+red (`tests/test_csv_export.py`, 15 cases) →\n14\t  code (`src/api/csv_export.py`: `EXPORT_HEADER`, `escape_csv_text_cell`,\n15\t  `format_window_start`, `format_total_quantity`) → green (15 passed).\n16\t- T2 Query schema: tests written+red (`tests/test_schemas_usage_export.py`, 13 cases) →\n17\t  code (`src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`: `UsageExportQueryParams`, reuses\n18\t  `CustomerId`/`Metric` from `src/api/schemas/events.py`, `from`-alias +\n19\t  `[now-90d, now+1h]` range validator) → green (13 passed).\n20\t- T3 Repository (integration-covered per plan's test-strategy tier bias, no\n21\t  dedicated unit file): extended `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` with\n22\t  `UsageRollupExportRecord`, `count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`\n23\t  (shared `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper, bound params only, fixed\n24\t  literal ORDER BY).\n25\t- T4 Service: tests written+red (`tests/test_usage_export_service.py`, 7 cases,\n26\t  DB mocked via monkeypatching `scoped_transaction`/`count_usage_rollups`/\n27\t  `stream_usage_rollups`) → code (`src/services/usage_export_service.py`:\n28\t  `prepare_export`, `stream_export_csv`, `MAX_EXPORT_ROWS=100_000`) → green\n29\t  (7 passed). Covers AC8/AC9/AC12/AC17/AC22 at the unit tier.\n30\t- T5 Route: `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (two-phase cap-then-stream,\n31\t  `responses=` OpenAPI metadata for the streamed 200/422 shapes), registered in\n32\t  `src/main.py` (`usage_export_router`, mounted between `usage_router` and\n33\t  `quotas_router`).\n34\t- T6 Integration: `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` — 18 tests,\n35\t  all green: header-only empty (AC12), filters incl. customer_id/metric/from-to\n36\t  and none-omitted-all (AC2), malformed/unknown query param 422 (AC4), auth 401\n37\t  + any-scope 200 (AC6), tenant isolation (AC7), row cap 422 no-partial-body\n38\t  (AC8), deterministic ordering (AC13), formula-injection end-to-end (AC10),\n39\t  response headers incl. strict filename regex (AC11), streaming-not-buffered\n40\t  via a real out-of-process uvicorn server (AC9 — `ASGITransport` was proven\n41\t  unusable for this, see Note below), OpenAPI schema exposure (AC19/DAST-1),\n42\t  forced pre-flight COUNT error -> generic 500 (AC22), and a dedicated\n43\t  two-principals-one-IP Tier-2 discriminator for this route (AC5).\n44\t- T7 Perf sanity: `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` (AC16) — green.\n45\t  Measures real p95 at 100,000 rows and asserts correctness (full,\n46\t  untruncated row set), following the project's `test_perf_smoke.py`\n47\t  honest-disclosure convention rather than hard-asserting the documented\n48\t  500ms budget (see Note below — real measured p95 is ~9.8s, far over\n49\t  budget, an honest open finding, not silently hidden or gated on).\n50\t- T8 Docs: updated `src/api/README.md`, `src/services/README.md`,\n51\t  `src/repositories/README.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md` (new\n52\t  `GET /v1/usage/export` request-flow section, mermaid diagram edge, and a\n53\t  \"Known deviations\" entry documenting the p95 finding). `PROJECT.md` was\n54\t  already updated by planning (feature description swapped from quotas to\n55\t  CSV export) — verified, not touched further.\n56\t\n57\t## Note — a real bug found and fixed during integration testing\n58\t\n59\t`httpx.ASGITransport`'s `ASGIResponseStream.__aiter__` does\n60\t`yield b\"\".join(self._body)` — it joins the ENTIRE response body into a single\n61\tchunk before the test ever sees it, regardless of how many times the app\n62\t`yield`s. This made the streaming-not-buffered sanity check meaningless against\n63\tthe in-process `client` fixture (chunk_count was always 1, pass or fail\n64\tindependent of real behavior). Fixed by adding a `running_server` fixture\n65\t(out-of-process uvicorn, mirrors `tests/integration/test_perf_smoke.py`'s\n66\tpattern) so the test observes genuine socket-level chunk boundaries. Also hit\n67\tthe documented `ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False)` requirement for the\n68\tAC22 forced-500 test (same pattern already established in\n69\t`tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py`'s AC19 test) — the default\n70\t`client` fixture re-raises app exceptions instead of returning the 500\n71\tresponse.\n72\t\n73\t## Note — honest perf finding (AC16, plan's Open Question 1)\n74\t\n75\tMeasured p95 for a full 100,000-row export (real Postgres testcontainer,\n76\tin-process ASGI) was **~9.8 seconds**, far over the plan's proposed-but-\n77\tunconfirmed 500ms target. Root cause is per-row Python-level CSV\n78\tencoding/escaping/formatting + generator overhead across 100k rows, not DB\n79\tquery time (the pre-flight COUNT and the bounded sort are both fast). This is\n80\tdisclosed in `docs/system_architecture.md`'s \"Known deviations\" section and\n81\tin the perf test's scratch-file measurement\n82\t(`meterly_usage_export_perf_measurement.json`), not silently hidden. The plan\n83\texplicitly left the 500ms number open pending checkpoint confirmation — this\n84\tis the data point for that decision, not a defect I introduced by deviating\n85\tfrom the plan's chosen design (server-side cursor + stdlib `csv`, which was\n86\tlocked in by the plan).\n87\t\n88\t## Verification performed this session\n89\t\n90\t- Full suite: `pytest tests -q --cov=src --cov-branch --deselect\n91\t  tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py` → **178 passed, 88% coverage**\n92\t  (gate is >=85%). `test_perf_k6_load.py` (4 tests, all pre-existing, none\n93\t  touching this feature's route) was deselected rather than run: verified\n94\t  this session via `which k6` that no k6 binary is on PATH in this sandbox,\n95\t  and via `--collect-only` that the 4 tests are unrelated to\n96\t  `GET /v1/usage/export` (they exercise `POST /v1/events` / `GET /v1/usage`\n97\t  under k6 load). Not run standalone to confirm its own skip/fail behavior —\n98\t  unverified beyond the binary-absence and unrelatedness checks above.\n99\t- Self-check (a): `git diff HEAD --name-only` + `git ls-files --others\n100\t  --exclude-standard` — every planned create/modify file is present: `PROJECT.md`,\n101\t  `docs/system_architecture.md`, `src/api/README.md`, `src/main.py`,\n102\t  `src/repositories/README.md`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`,\n103\t  `src/services/README.md` (modified); `src/api/csv_export.py`,\n104\t  `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`,\n105\t  `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, plus the 5 test files (new,\n106\t  untracked). No planned file missing; no stray files (transient\n107\t  `.coverage.*` worker artifacts from local test runs were deleted).\n108\t- Self-check (b) hardcoded secrets: `grep -rniE\n109\t  \"(api_key|apikey|token|secret|password|credentials)\\s*=\\s*['\\\"][^'\\\"]{8,}\"`\n110\t  across all changed files → no matches.\n111\t- Self-check (b) RLS scoping: confirmed `count_usage_rollups` and\n112\t  `stream_usage_rollups` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`) both start their\n113\t  WHERE clause with `api_key_id = :api_key_id` via the shared\n114\t  `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper; `api_key_id` is sourced only from\n115\t  `principal.api_key_id` in the service, never from client input.\n116\t- Self-check (b) unsanitized inputs: confirmed the only new HTTP input\n117\t  surface (`GET /v1/usage/export` query params) is bound through\n118\t  `Annotated[UsageExportQueryParams, Query()]` in\n119\t  `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` — schema-first, `extra=\"forbid\"`, reused\n120\t  anchored-allowlist `constr` types for `customer_id`/`metric`.\n121\t- Self-check (c) acceptance criteria: all 22 criteria in\n122\t  `.pipeline/acceptance.md` are addressed — AC1-AC17, AC19-AC22 built and\n123\t  test-covered (unit and/or integration, mapped in T1-T7 above); AC18 is\n124\t  delegated to the security stage per the plan's frontmatter\n125\t  (`delegated_criteria: [AC18]`), not built here by design.\n126\t\n127\tNo migration needed (plan: `migration_added: false`, read-only feature, no\n128\tnew stored data). No `infra/` change. `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` already\n129\twritten (new entry point, new CSV-formula trust boundary, new DB queries/log\n130\tevent, new-but-matching-existing-shape authz surface).\n131\t"}]},"uuid":"0c6f5eb4-b960-4527-bccf-a978d89c8028","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:27:56.005Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f533531c-7e8c-42a0-aeee-c33b098c4f33","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
