{"parentUuid":"b8a0940e-6083-474e-bddb-7528e6eae2b6","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs31kSZSdHFX9BemZ4et","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JCsyA9Q5dTQRvuDpcigVvk","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\acceptance.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2820,"cache_read_input_tokens":28596,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2820,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs31jN4ickTGtVVDjv3Y","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"e751db71-c36f-43ea-8122-5bfa7eb585b5","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:28:42.413Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"e751db71-c36f-43ea-8122-5bfa7eb585b5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed4149fd-c5a8-4db4-bdd2-38a556acc251","agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JCsyA9Q5dTQRvuDpcigVvk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tfeature: usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\n3\tcriteria_total: 22\n4\tdelegated_criteria: [AC18]\n5\tderived_from: PROJECT.md + .pipeline/requirements.md (resolved items) + STRIDE + input-surface + DAST-readiness\n6\tnotes: >\n7\t  Feature-level definition-of-done. Implementation builds to these; testing maps each ID to a\n8\t  test (criteria_covered). AC18 is delegated to the security stage (ASVS reconciliation), so\n9\t  testing marks it covered:false, delegated:\"security\". No performance k6 load AC: the export is\n10\t  a reporting route with a documented p95 sanity check (AC16); the binding perf constraint is the\n11\t  negative one (AC15 — existing endpoints/budgets untouched). AC22 (added in the revision pass)\n12\t  covers the pre-flight safe-error shape — distinct from plan §R3, which only accepts the\n13\t  post-200 mid-stream truncation case.\n14\t---\n15\t\n16\t| ID | Criterion | File / layer | How verified |\n17\t|---|---|---|---|\n18\t| AC1 | Response is RFC 4180 CSV via stdlib `csv`: header row exactly `customer_id,metric,window_start,total_quantity` (brief column order), CRLF line endings, fields containing comma/quote/newline quoted | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit (dialect, header, CRLF, quoting) + integration end-to-end body assertion |\n19\t| AC2 | Optional `customer_id`/`metric`/`from`/`to` filters applied (reusing existing allowlist types + window bounds); all omitted → full supported range | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Unit (schema) + integration (each filter narrows the row set; none → all caller rows) |\n20\t| AC3 | `from`/`to` validation: timezone-aware, `from <= to`, both within `[now-90d, now+1h]`, naive datetime rejected | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py` | Unit (accept/reject cases incl. naive, inverted range, out-of-window) |\n21\t| AC4 | Input validation (non-waivable): malformed / wrong-type / unknown / out-of-range query param → 422 `validation_failed`; `extra=\"forbid\"` rejects unknown params | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | Unit + integration (422 envelope with `code=validation_failed`) |\n22\t| AC5 | Rate limit: post-auth **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** throttle applies (principal-keyed); two principals on one client IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (reuses `src/auth/rate_limit.py`) | Integration two-principals-one-IP discriminating test |\n23\t| AC6 | Authorization: any authenticated key (ingest or admin) may export; unauthenticated/invalid → 401; no scope gate | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/auth` | Integration (ingest key 200, admin key 200, no/invalid key 401) |\n24\t| AC7 | Tenant isolation: export returns ONLY the caller's `api_key_id` rows; two tenants' data never cross (explicit `api_key_id` filter is the primary control; RLS is backstop) | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration two-tenant test (tenant A's export excludes tenant B's rows) |\n25\t| AC8 | Row cap: a result exceeding 100,000 rows → 422 `validation_failed` (\"narrow filters\"), **no partial body streamed** (pre-flight count before any response byte) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (>100k rows → 422, response body is the envelope not CSV) |\n26\t| AC9 | Streaming constant memory: rows streamed as read via a server-side cursor, response not fully buffered before send | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration streaming-not-buffered sanity (first bytes observable before generator exhausted / bounded memory on a large export) |\n27\t| AC10 | CSV formula-injection escape: text cells (`customer_id`,`metric`) starting with `= + - @ \\t \\r` prefixed with `'`; control chars neutralized; numeric/timestamp cells untouched | `src/api/csv_export.py` | Unit (incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, each trigger, control chars, numeric/timestamp unaffected) + integration end-to-end |\n28\t| AC11 | Response headers: `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8`; `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv` (no tenant identifier in filename); inherits `nosniff` + `Cache-Control: no-store` | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/middleware.py` | Integration header assertions (incl. filename pattern, no tenant id) |\n29\t| AC12 | Empty result → 200 header-only CSV (single header row, zero data rows), never 404 | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration (caller with no matching rollups → 200, one CSV line) |\n30\t| AC13 | Deterministic ordering `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC`; identical exports are byte-stable | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (asserts row order over a seeded multi-row set) |\n31\t| AC14 | Value formats: `window_start` as UTC ISO-8601 with offset (identical to JSON response form); `total_quantity` as `str(Decimal)` (plain decimal, no scientific notation) | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit + integration (format assertions) |\n32\t| AC15 | No behavior change: `POST /v1/events`, `GET /v1/usage`, `PUT /v1/quotas` behavior/budgets/tests unchanged; no new Alembic revision / migration added | repo-wide (negative) | Existing test suites pass unchanged; no new file under `alembic/versions/` |\n33\t| AC16 | Performance budget: export route **p95 < 500 ms at the 100,000-row cap** (documented target, integration timing sanity — NOT a k6 load AC) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration timing sanity test at ~100k rows |\n34\t| AC17 | Audit logging: exactly one `usage.export` `info` event at completion (`userId`=opaque `api_key_id`, `operation`, `rowCount`, `capped`, `completed`, filter-presence booleans — no raw `customer_id`); over-cap request logged at `warn` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/logging` | Unit/integration (log fields present, no PII, one event; `warn` on over-cap) |\n35\t| AC18 | ASVS 5.0 L1/L2 controls for the triggered chapters (V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V13/V14/V16) present across the change set; recorded waivers honored | cross-cutting | Delegated to security stage (`delegated:\"security\"`) — reconciled against plan §ASVS Compliance |\n36\t| AC19 (DAST-1) | Served OpenAPI schema includes `GET /v1/usage/export` with its `200 text/csv` and `422` responses, matching the implemented route (not hand-drifted) | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Integration (assert route + responses present in `/openapi.json`) |\n37\t| AC20 (DAST-2) | A seeded non-production DAST test key (reuse the existing seeded key; credentials from env/secrets, never hardcoded) can call the export | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` (existing), test fixtures | Integration (seeded key successfully hits the export in staging/local) |\n38\t| AC21 (DAST-3) | Auth-context recorded for scanners: `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` header shape, documented in the plan and exercised by the integration auth path | plan §Auth, `src/auth/api_key.py` (existing) | Documented in plan + integration test uses this exact Bearer shape |\n39\t| AC22 | Safe-error / fail-closed pre-flight: a forced internal error during the pre-flight `prepare_export` `COUNT` phase (before any response byte) returns the generic `500 internal` error-envelope (no stack/SQL/internal path leaked), rolls back the transaction, and starts **no** stream / emits **no** partial CSV body (ASVS 16.5.x). Distinct from plan §R3 (post-200 mid-stream truncation, accepted) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py`, `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Unit in `tests/test_usage_export_service.py` (non-cap DB error propagates, not swallowed, no stream started) + integration in `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` (forced pre-flight `COUNT` error → `500 internal` envelope, no leak, no partial body) |\n40\t"}]},"uuid":"e6b1f896-dc49-430c-a33e-97b9e643787b","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:28:42.432Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e751db71-c36f-43ea-8122-5bfa7eb585b5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"e6b1f896-dc49-430c-a33e-97b9e643787b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs31kSZSdHFX9BemZ4et","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FUPqnMczL8b5YJ2FSVqqRN","name":"Grep","input":{"pattern":"Known deviations","path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md","output_mode":"content","-n":true,"-A":30},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2820,"cache_read_input_tokens":28596,"output_tokens":2444,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2820},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":2444,"cache_read_input_tokens":28596,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2820,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2820,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs31jN4ickTGtVVDjv3Y","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"b5972c7e-716c-45a7-a87a-124d21bf6754","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:28:43.843Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"b5972c7e-716c-45a7-a87a-124d21bf6754","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed4149fd-c5a8-4db4-bdd2-38a556acc251","agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FUPqnMczL8b5YJ2FSVqqRN","type":"tool_result","content":"226:## Known deviations / accepted risks\n227-\n228-See `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` for the rate-limit fail-open behavior and the\n229-OTel/Sentry wiring-at-construction-time change vs. the plan's original\n230-lifespan-hook placement. See `plan.md`'s \"Open questions\" section for the\n231-accepted risks around key-revocation latency, `api_key_id`-as-tenant-scope,\n232-and the Postgres app-role bootstrap's CI-network-reachability prerequisite.\n233-\n234-**`GET /v1/usage/export` p95 measurement vs. the documented 500ms target\n235-(plan §\"Open questions\" #1, unresolved — flagged, not silently accepted).**\n236-`tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` measures real p95 latency for\n237-a full 100,000-row export end to end (real Postgres testcontainer, in-process\n238-ASGI transport) rather than asserting the documented 500ms budget, per the\n239-project's existing honest-disclosure convention\n240-(`tests/integration/test_perf_smoke.py`). The measured p95 in this sandboxed\n241-dev environment was **~9.8 seconds** — far outside the documented 500ms\n242-target, driven by per-row Python-level CSV encoding/formatting/escaping and\n243-generator overhead across 100,000 rows, not primarily DB query time (the\n244-pre-flight `COUNT` and the bounded 100k-row sort are both fast). This is a\n245-real architectural cost of the per-row stdlib-`csv` streaming design the plan\n246-chose (constant memory, single DB snapshot) traded against raw throughput at\n247-the row cap; it is not an artifact of this specific sandboxed run alone. The\n248-plan explicitly left the 500ms number as an *open, unconfirmed* target\n249-pending checkpoint confirmation — this measurement is the data point that\n250-confirms or adjusts it. Follow-up options if 500ms is confirmed as binding:\n251-batch multiple rows per `csv.writer` flush, or reconsider the per-row\n252-escape/format call overhead; out of scope for this slice to change\n253-unilaterally since the plan fixed the streaming design."}]},"uuid":"03cb5298-10b7-4b1d-85a2-2464b2022492","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:28:43.938Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b5972c7e-716c-45a7-a87a-124d21bf6754","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
