{"parentUuid":"392ec1bc-4e76-4c5a-a47a-c944d8a8c167","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed4149fd-c5a8-4db4-bdd2-38a556acc251","agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FeZhEELvhcsvNMKmRwr9Qb","type":"tool_result","content":"=== encoding microbench (AFTER escape fix) ===\nrecords=100000\r\ncurrent (per-row encode+chunk)       245.9 ms   chunks=100001\r\n\r\n\n=== csv_export + service unit tests ===\nC:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\pytest_asyncio\\plugin.py:207: PytestDeprecationWarning: The configuration option \"asyncio_default_fixture_loop_scope\" is unset.\r\nThe event loop scope for asynchronous fixtures will default to the fixture caching scope. Future versions of pytest-asyncio will default the loop scope for asynchronous fixtures to function scope. Set the default fixture loop scope explicitly in order to avoid unexpected behavior in the future. Valid fixture loop scopes are: \"function\", \"class\", \"module\", \"package\", \"session\"\r\n\r\n  warnings.warn(PytestDeprecationWarning(_DEFAULT_FIXTURE_LOOP_SCOPE_UNSET))\r\n....................................                                     [100%]\r\n============================== warnings summary ===============================\r\ntests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_prepare_export_rejects_over_cap_with_422\r\n  C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\test_usage_export_service.py:75: StarletteDeprecationWarning: 'HTTP_422_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY' is deprecated. Use 'HTTP_422_UNPROCESSABLE_CONTENT' instead.\r\n    await usage_export_service.prepare_export(_principal(), _no_filter_params())\r\n\r\n-- Docs: https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/capture-warnings.html\r\n36 passed, 1 warning in 1.34s","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"aba5ad71-11ab-4465-aba8-0059160e7eed","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:45:41.051Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"392ec1bc-4e76-4c5a-