{"parentUuid":"0e631e40-8c7a-4d3a-9b61-f5f16731289f","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs5FXLdyiJqcVUb3jQwY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NDLqwf98CZu61HSnKkcjXb","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\usage_export_service.py","offset":88,"limit":70},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":302,"cache_read_input_tokens":158345,"output_tokens":273,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":302},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":273,"cache_read_input_tokens":158345,"cache_creation_input_tokens":302,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":302,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs5FT2vUfwbCxdoFUkJT","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"08b559f3-9d08-4968-be37-7bfefb0418fd","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:57:33.149Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"08b559f3-9d08-4968-be37-7bfefb0418fd","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed4149fd-c5a8-4db4-bdd2-38a556acc251","agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NDLqwf98CZu61HSnKkcjXb","type":"tool_result","content":"88\t    return data\n89\t\n90\t\n91\tasync def stream_export_csv(\n92\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal, params: UsageExportQueryParams\n93\t) -> AsyncIterator[bytes]:\n94\t    \"\"\"The `StreamingResponse` body: the header row first, always, then one\n95\t    CSV-encoded row per streamed `usage_rollup` record.\n96\t\n97\t    Yielding the header before touching the database means an empty result\n98\t    is still a 200 header-only CSV, never a 404 (AC12, mirrors the existing\n99\t    zeros-not-404 contract on `GET /v1/usage`). Opens its own tenant-scoped\n100\t    transaction so the `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id` RLS-backstop\n101\t    setting and the server-side cursor both stay valid for the whole stream.\n102\t    \"\"\"\n103\t    row_count = 0\n104\t    capped = False\n105\t    completed = False\n106\t\n107\t    buffer = io.StringIO()\n108\t    writer = csv.writer(buffer, lineterminator=\"\\r\\n\", quoting=csv.QUOTE_MINIMAL)\n109\t\n110\t    try:\n111\t        # Header first, always, as its own chunk — so an empty result is a\n112\t        # 200 header-only CSV (AC12) and the first bytes are observable before\n113\t        # the data rows stream (AC9), independent of the data-row batching below.\n114\t        writer.writerow(EXPORT_HEADER)\n115\t        yield _drain(buffer)\n116\t\n117\t        async with scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id) as session:\n118\t            async for record in stream_usage_rollups(\n119\t                session,\n120\t                api_key_id=principal.api_key_id,\n121\t                customer_id=params.customer_id,\n122\t                metric=params.metric,\n123\t                window_from=params.from_,\n124\t                window_to=params.to,\n125\t                limit=MAX_EXPORT_ROWS,\n126\t            ):\n127\t                writer.writerow(\n128\t                    [\n129\t                        escape_csv_text_cell(record.customer_id),\n130\t                        escape_csv_text_cell(record.metric),\n131\t                        format_window_start(record.window_start),\n132\t                        format_total_quantity(record.total_quantity),\n133\t                    ]\n134\t                )\n135\t                row_count += 1\n136\t                # Hand a chunk to the ASGI stack once per _ROWS_PER_CHUNK rows,\n137\t                # not once per row (see _ROWS_PER_CHUNK). Still streaming: at the\n138\t                # cap this yields ~100 chunks, never one buffered blob.\n139\t                if row_count % _ROWS_PER_CHUNK == 0:\n140\t                    yield _drain(buffer)\n141\t\n142\t        # Flush the trailing partial batch. For an empty result nothing is\n143\t        # buffered here (the header already went out above), so no stray chunk.\n144\t        if buffer.tell():\n145\t            yield _drain(buffer)\n146\t\n147\t        capped = row_count >= MAX_EXPORT_ROWS\n148\t        completed = True\n149\t    finally:\n150\t        # In `finally` so a client disconnect or a mid-stream DB error still\n151\t        # records what was actually sent (`completed=False` in that case) —\n152\t        # exactly one usage.export event per request either way (AC17).\n153\t        logger.info(\n154\t            \"usage.export\",\n155\t            userId=principal.api_key_id,\n156\t            action=\"read\",\n157\t            resource=\"usage_rollup\","}]},"uuid":"5fe9914c-d912-4966-a412-c7d3cc819876","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:57:33.176Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"08b559f3-9d08-4968-be37-7bfefb0418fd","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"5fe9914c-d912-4966-a412-c7d3cc819876","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs5FraGnQMz8FeJs8afp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1454,"cache_read_input_tokens":158647,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1454,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs5FqHsxwTwkZhgDUmYH","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"07b27994-3d7f-4860-ba6a-9163411ad8e9","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:57:58.524Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"07b27994-3d7f-4860-ba6a-9163411ad8e9","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3e97ca51fd7e87e","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs5FraGnQMz8FeJs8afp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The batching logic is coherent and handles all edge cases (exact-multiple last batch → no stray chunk; empty result → header-only). All fixes are verified in place, no debug probes leaked, and the affected suites are green (37 unit + 20 integration).\n\n## Summary\n\n**Finding (AC16):** `GET /v1/usage/export` p95 at the 100,000-row cap was ~50x over the plan's proposed 500 ms target (testing measured 25,210 ms; my baseline re-measure this session was 10,720 ms). Fixed as a remediation-role patch.\n\n**Reproduced first:** ran `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` → baseline p95 **10,720.92 ms**, `meets_documented_budget: false`.\n\n**Root cause (measured, not assumed — the disclosure was only partly right):** I profiled every layer in isolation. Pure CSV encoding was only ~360 ms and the DB drain ~1 s — neither is the ~10 s. The dominant cost is the **chunk-per-row streaming pattern**: the generator did `yield` **per row** (100,001 chunks at the cap), and the app stack in `src/main.py` has **four nested Starlette `BaseHTTPMiddleware`** layers, each of which re-pumps every streamed chunk through its own anyio memory-object-stream. Cost ≈ (chunk count × middleware layers), so it exploded at the cap. A minimal-app benchmark (no middleware) ran the same real path in ~1.6 s; adding 4 `BaseHTTPMiddleware` layers reproduced ~6.9 s. The server-side `request.completed` log confirmed the handler *returns* in 16–94 ms — the time is all post-return streaming.\n\n**Fix (minimal, within the human-approved design — server-side cursor / pre-flight COUNT / 100k cap / OWASP escape all preserved):**\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\usage_export_service.py` — **batch rows per chunk** (`_ROWS_PER_CHUNK = 1000`); header still yielded first as its own chunk (AC12/AC9). ~101 chunks at the cap instead of 100,001. **Primary lever.**\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\csv_export.py` — replaced the per-character Python strip loop in `escape_csv_text_cell` with a precomputed C-level `str.translate` table. Semantics **identical** (0 mismatches across all codepoints 0x00–0x11F + combos; unchanged AC10 tests). Encoding 360 → 246 ms.\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\usage_repo.py` — `yield_per=5000` on the server-side cursor (tunes fetch batch, does not abandon the cursor). DB drain 1,014 → 609 ms.\n\n**Proven:** regression test `tests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_stream_export_csv_batches_rows_into_few_chunks` (fails-before: per-row impl = 5,001 chunks; passes-after: 6 chunks, byte-identical CSV) — fails-before confirmed via a scratch reproduction (real tree never reverted), passes-after **12/12** runs. No regressions: **37** unit + **20** integration tests green (AC9 streaming and AC10 escape included).\n\n**Before → after p95 at the cap (real perf test, full app stack):** **10,720 ms (25,210 ms testing) → ~1.4 s median / ~2.0 s p95** (stable 10-sample: min 1,139 / median 1,374 / p95 2,073 ms). **~7–17x faster**; anti-pattern eliminated.\n\n**Escalation — budget decision is the human's (not a self-redesign):** even after this genuine optimization pass, p95 (~1.4–2.0 s) still exceeds the **proposed** 500 ms. The residual is irreducible work *within* the approved design: draining 100k rows over the mandated server-side cursor is ~0.6 s even tuned (a buffered `fetchall`, which would abandon the constant-memory cursor, is ~0.32 s), plus ~0.25 s Python CSV encoding — a floor of ~0.85–1.0 s with the cursor. So **500 ms is not achievable at the 100k cap within this design.** Per the constraint I did **not** weaken AC16 or fabricate a pass; the perf test still records the honest p95 (`meets_documented_budget: false`). The 500 ms figure is plan Open Question 1 (unconfirmed) — the human decides whether to relax it to the achieved number or confirm it as binding, which would require a **redesign** (planning escalation), not a patch.\n\n**Bookkeeping:** `.pipeline/debug-notes.md` written (full hypothesis log — file didn't exist); `.pipeline/state.json` `remediation` count 0 → 1 (cap 3). Per the remediation loop, **testing and security still need their post-remediation re-run** (full suite + scan) — I authored the single fix-locking regression test, not the full-suite revalidation, which testing owns."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1454,"cache_read_input_tokens":158647,"output_tokens":3463,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1454},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":3463,"cache_read_input_tokens":158647,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1454,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1454,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs5FqHsxwTwkZhgDUmYH","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"e8dd0108-b741-4ff3-abb2-27c8907f901e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:58:19.644Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
